3.1 Describe the code above in your R markdown file, and then put it in an R chunk and run it.

This code uses rowwise() to do a chi-square test on each row
of the dataset and adds a new column called chisq_stat which means
the chi-square test statistic.


```{r}
mendel_data <- mendel_data %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(chisq_stat = chisq.test(c(n1, n2),
                                 p = c(p0, 1 - p0))$statistic)

mendel_data

```



